    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Momentum Rotation",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum rotation means selling stocks that are losing their upward momentum (falling MACD, price below moving averages) and reinvesting that capital into stocks showing stronger momentum signals. Investors do this to keep their portfolio aligned with where market strength actually is, rather than holding on to weakening positions hoping they recover. Today we rotated out of COIN and NVDA (both score 30, bearish) and into AMZN (score 90, bullish) for exactly this reason.",
